The minister of Humanitarian affairs and disaster management,Sadiya Umar Farouq has penned a message of gratitude to Batches A and B beneficiaries of Npower, a socio-investment programme of the federal government. In a statement released on her twitter handle, she expressed gratitude to the beneficiaries and congratulated about 109,823 beneficiaries of Batch A and B for using the opportunity to set up businesses in their communities. She noted that the transitioning and exit of batch A and B which begins today, June 30 and terminates July 31 is  not a punitive action. A short note of gratitude from me to @npower_ng Batch A and B beneficiaries. pic.twitter.com/vZl7sqztv6